TY  - JOUR
AU  - Harris, Milton
AU  - Raviv, Artur
T1  - Control of Corporate Decisions: Shareholders vs. Management
PY  - 2010
Y1  - 2010/11/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhq081
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 23
IS  - 11
SP  - 4115
EP  - 4147
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - This article addresses the issue of whether shareholders would be better off with enhanced control over corporate decisions. The issue has been hotly debated in the recent literature. Our main contribution is to use formal modeling to uncover some factors overlooked in these arguments. For example, we show that claims that shareholder control would reduce value because shareholders lack sufficient information to make important decisions or because they have a non-value-maximizing agenda are flawed. We also show, however, that even if shareholders seek to maximize firm value and can delegate decisions to management, shareholders should not control all major decisions.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhq081
ER  - 



